The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 19 April is 271,403 (31,280.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 14 April, there were 3,073 new confirmed cases (354.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 April, there were 4,349 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 29% (1,276 fewer cases).
